                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/4188: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-27T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 27, 1934—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. Your 275, September 27, 9 a.m. In reply to the inquiry addressed to you, you
                    may state confidentially and informally that while the United States is unable
                    to participate in the proposed League Chaco Commission, this Government, acting
                    in its individual capacity, will adopt a friendly and cooperative attitude
                    towards the activities of the Commission whenever in its own judgment such
                    attitude may prove of practical assistance in furthering the pacific solution of
                    the Chaco problem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
